                <tr> <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="main text" --> 
                  <td align="left" valign="top" class="bodytext"> <p>In the Andrew Kean Learning Centre, you will have full access to a wide range of study support facilities including: </p>
                    <ul>
                      <li>Computing Help Desk
                      <li>Library Enquiry Desk
                      <li>Seating for 184 students
                      <li>Four dedicated IT rooms
                      <li>A large 24/7 IT room
                      <li>152 personal computers
                      <li>Full Internet and Electronic Mail
                      <li>Library book stock
                      <li>Reference materials and journals
                      <li>Dedicated group study rooms
                      <li>Quiet study facilities
                      <li>Study carrels
                      <li>Photocopiers
                      <li>Mono and Colour laser printing
                      <li>Automated student print management
                      <li>Scanning facilities
                      <li>Interactive whiteboards
                      <li>Separate phone zone and refreshments area </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>The 24/7 IT facility contains 34 high specification PC's and is available around the clock throughout the year. </p>                    <p class="bodytext"><span class="subtitle">Laptops</span><br>
                      These are available for hire for use within the Learning Centre. Please enquire at the Library counter for more information </p>
                    <p class="bodytext"><strong>24-Hour IT suite</strong><br>
    This is available 24 hours each day, year round. <a href="http://www.tasc.ac.uk/iss/itservices/Computing_rooms.htm">See list of all college IT facilities</a></p>                    <p class="bodytext"><strong>Room Bookings</strong><br>
  All library IT rooms may be booked for contact teaching purposes through the central college room bookings facility, tel. 0113 283 2197. </p>
                    <p class="bodytext">Student group study rooms may be booked by any registered college student through the Library Counter Services Desk, tel. 0113 283 7244 </p>
                    <p class="bodytext"><strong>Interactive Whiteboard facilities</strong></p>
                    <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="31%" class="bodytext"><img src="images/facilities4.jpg" width="113" height="113"></td>
                        <td width="69%" class="bodytext">&#8216;SMARTBOARD&#8217; multimedia whiteboards are available in each of the four ground floor library based IT rooms and in the largest first floor group study room. The whiteboards may be used by staff and students. Library Counter Services provide support packs which include special water based dry markers and electronic pens for use with these facilities. </td>
                      </tr>
                    </table>
                    <p class="bodytext"><strong>Printing facilities</strong><br>
  The Learning Centre delivers printing through a new <a href="http://www.tasc.ac.uk/iss/itservices/Print.htm">integrated print credit system</a>. Students use an ATM style unit located in the ground floor photocopying area to &#8216;top up&#8217; their electronic printing accounts. Students can direct their printing requirements to any of the colour or mono laser printers available at various locations in the library and in each IT room.</p>
                    <p class="bodytext"><strong>Photocopying facilities</strong><br>
                    </p>
                    <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                      <tr>
                        <td width="30%" class="bodytext"><img src="images/facilitiespic1.jpg" width="113" height="113"></td>
                        <td width="70%" class="bodytext">Photocopiers are available on the ground and first floors, and copy cards may be purchased from the wall-mounted dispenser adjacent to the ground floor photocopiers. The Library Counter Services Desk offers a laminating service, and guillotines, electric staplers and binding machines are available adjacent to the photocopiers on each floor.</td>
                      </tr>
                    </table>
                    <p><span class="subtitle">Disabled Students</span><br>
                    The Learning Centre has been designed to support disabled students. Access to the upper floors is available by a centrally located lift. Dedicated areas have been assigned within the Centre to accommodate the needs of dyslexic and disabled students. A leaflet giving full details of arrangements for users with disabilities is available from the Library Counter on the Ground floor. </p>
                    <p>To support the needs of all students, the Learning Centre is a designated <strong>quiet zone </strong>. Food and drink are not allowed and smoking is prohibited in the Centre. All mobile phones must be switched off before you enter the Learning Centre. </p>
                    <p>All users of LIS facilities are required to comply with the <strong><a href="http://www.tasc.ac.uk/iss/library/accept.htm">LIS Acceptable Use Policy</a></strong> , a printed copy of which can be found on the Centre's various information boards and in the Policies section of the <a href="http://www.tasc.ac.uk/handbook">student handbook</a>.</p>                    
                    <p class="bodytext">&nbsp;</p>
